						<summary>

						<p>On a fourth slab found in Vishṇu temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1203, Uttarāyaṇa-Saṁkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Registers the grant of 8 cows by Anna-Pērakā, wife of Devara-Paṇḍita for the maintenance of half a lamp in the temple of Nagarīśvara. The cows were kept in the custody of Anne-peddi family.</p>						

